    <title>Detector control system for CBM-TOF</title>
    <summary>  For charged hadron identification, a high-performance Time-Of-Flight (TOF)
RPC wall is being built for the CBM experiment at FAIR. The detector control
system (DCS) for CBM-TOF is designed based on EPICS. Instruments, including
power supplies, power supply distributors, and gas control systems, are
controlled and monitored in a CBM full system test-setup called mCBM
(mini-CBM). For monitoring the environment of the detector in a radiant
environment and the status of front-end electronics (FEE), a slow control
application is implemented based on IPbus, which is an FPGA-based slow control
bus also used in TOF fast data acquisition (DAQ) system. Besides the functions
of controlling and monitoring, exception handling and data archiving functions
are also implemented. This control system was fully verified in beam tests in
2019 at GSI.
</summary>
